ell are the proud parents Of a

Mrs. Bonnie Hunter Watson
and her daughter. Robin are re-
covering from injuries received

on the highway near Florence two
weeks ago and Bonnie suffered
broken back. Robin has broken
leg.


Mr.. and Mrs. Pleasant John
son, hosted gala party at their
loyelv home. 1925 E.. Coronado
Rd. for operators of the Ad-
rianne Beauty Salon.


Guests included Mr.. and Mrs.
Melvin Gray, Mrs. Johnny Con-
ner, who was honored on her
birthday, too, Miss Alnetta Faye
Hawkins, MIR. and Mrs. Jessie
Ruffin. Mr.. and Mrs. Fred Oliver,
Mr.. and Mrs. W. T. Turner,
Mr.. and Mrs. James Reed, Mr..
and Mrs. Lyle Allen. Mr.. Ron
ME Smart, Mrs. Katie Clark,
Mrs. Richie Mae Mark and Miss
Joy Minnefield.


The delicious food was pre-
pared by Mrs. Bertha Rollins,
Mrs. Johns on's mother. She had
something new to me monkey
bread.


Thought of the week; Patience
is the companion of wisdom.

Hot weather grand time for The ice and punch
refreshing and cooling


From the looks the faces the honoree and guests
great affair.


Jones' MIR. and Mrs Joel Shambra 1906 E.
Wood St., celebrated his thirteenth year.


Joining Paul Anderson, Shirley McCun Areddie
Brooks Ne Williams Jasper Hendrix Leonard Binyeard Or
land Pete, Sheriff. Jones, and Patricia McCuin.
